#. type: Plain text
#: ../../calc.texi:7523
msgid ""
"For the list @expr{[a, b, c, d]}, the result is @expr{((a = b) = c) = d}, "
"which will compare @expr{a} and @expr{b} to produce a 1 or 0, which is then "
"compared with @expr{c} to produce another 1 or 0, which is then compared "
